# Software Requirements Document for Shopify Store Inspiration Tool

## 1. Executive Summary
This document outlines the requirements for a Shopify Store Inspiration Tool aimed at assisting users in generating ideas and inspiration for creating their own Shopify stores. The tool will provide users with curated resources, articles, and examples of successful Shopify stores, focusing on low-cost and unique business ideas. The goal is to empower aspiring entrepreneurs with the knowledge and inspiration needed to establish their online presence effectively.

## 2. Project Overview
The Shopify Store Inspiration Tool will serve as a web-based application that aggregates various resources related to Shopify store creation. It will include articles on business ideas, examples of successful stores, and unique concepts that can be implemented by users. The application will be designed to be user-friendly and accessible, ensuring that users can easily navigate through the content and find relevant information.

## 3. Functional Requirements
### 3.1 User Interface
- The application shall have a clean and intuitive user interface.
- Users shall be able to navigate through different categories of business ideas.
- Users shall be able to search for specific topics or keywords.

### 3.2 Content Aggregation
- The application shall provide links to articles on low-cost business ideas.
- The application shall feature a section for successful Shopify store examples.
- The application shall include unique and home business ideas.

### 3.3 User Interaction
- Users shall be able to save their favorite articles for future reference.
- Users shall have the option to share articles on social media platforms.

### 3.4 Feedback Mechanism
- The application shall allow users to provide feedback on the usefulness of the resources.
- Users shall be able to rate articles and resources.

## 4. Non-Functional Requirements
### 4.1 Performance
- The application shall load within 3 seconds on a standard broadband connection.
- The application shall support at least 1000 concurrent users without performance degradation.

### 4.2 Usability
- The application shall be designed for ease of use, with a focus on user experience.
- The application shall be accessible to users with disabilities, complying with WCAG 2.1 standards.

### 4.3 Security
- The application shall ensure that user data is securely stored and transmitted.
- The application shall implement measures to prevent unauthorized access.

## 5. User Stories
### 5.1 As a user, I want to:
- Browse through different categories of business ideas so that I can find inspiration for my Shopify store.
- Save articles that I find useful so that I can easily access them later.
- Share interesting articles with my friends on social media.

### 5.2 As an administrator, I want to:
- Update the content regularly to ensure that users have access to the latest information.
- Monitor user feedback to improve the quality of the resources provided.

## 6. Acceptance Criteria
- The application must allow users to navigate through at least 5 different categories of business ideas.
- Users must be able to save and retrieve at least 10 articles in their favorites list.
- The application must provide a feedback mechanism with at least 80% positive feedback on the usefulness of resources.

## 7. Assumptions and Constraints
### 7.1 Assumptions
- Users have basic internet access and familiarity with web applications.
- The application will be developed using standard web technologies (HTML, CSS, JavaScript).

### 7.2 Constraints
- The project must be completed within a 3-month timeline.
- The budget for the project is limited to $50,000.

## 8. Glossary of Terms
- **Shopify**: A leading e-commerce platform that allows individuals and businesses to create their own online stores.
- **User Interface (UI)**: The means by which a user interacts with a computer or software application.
- **WCAG**: Web Content Accessibility Guidelines, a set of recommendations for making web content more accessible to people with disabilities.

---

This document serves as a foundational guide for the development team and stakeholders, ensuring that all parties have a clear understanding of the project's objectives and requirements.